### PUT /follow/:userId

This endpoint is used to update the follow status for a specific user.

#### Request

- Method: PUT

- Base URL: {{USER_BASE_URL}}

- Path: /follow/:userId

- Headers:
    - Content-Type: application/json

- Body:
    - name (string, optional): The name of the user to be followed.


#### Response

- Status: 200

- Content-Type: application/json

- Body:

    ``` json
      {
          "status": true,
          "data": {
              "message": ""
          }
      }

     ```


#### JSON Schema

``` json
{
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "status": {
            "type": "boolean"
        },
        "data": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "message": {
                    "type": "string"
                }
            }
        }
    }
}

 ```

### Update Unfollow Status
This endpoint is used to unfollow a user by their ID.

#### Request
- Method: PUT
- URL: `{{USER_BASE_URL}}/unfollow/:userId`
- Body:
  - name (string, optional): The name of the user to unfollow.

#### Response
The response is in JSON format with the following schema:
```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "status": {
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "data": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "message": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```
- Status: 200 OK
- Content-Type: application/json
- status (boolean): Indicates the success status of the unfollow operation.
- data.message (string): A message confirming the unfollow action.

